The flood situation in Bangladesh is dire, with millions displaced and at least 40 reported deaths.
Major rivers like the Ganges and Brahmaputra are swelling, threatening central regions.
Evacuations are underway, with soldiers and volunteers distributing aid.
In the past week, over 5 million people have been affected, and the situation is expected to worsen.
The UK has pledged $2.5 million in aid to assist with relief efforts.
The flood forecasting center warns of further inundation in multiple districts, emphasizing the urgent need for assistance in the face of this devastating natural disaster.
